I think the reason you are getting some criticism from other users is simply due to a lack of clarity in describing the exact nature of this Win 8 Torrent.

In other words, you should have noted that it was the "Release Preview" and/or the Build (8400)number. 

Many people are wanting to activate the RTM version and I know I clicked this link solely with that in mind - Knowing all to well that something had to be amiss .. and it was 

For the record, I am dual booting win 8 x64 b-8400 & RTM b-9200 ..  and I DO use the 8400 build primarily, but it's not for a lack of stability that I do so.

The RTM(FINAL) Version has actually removed a few key features that I consider important. 
Gadgets(Win Sidebar) and, although hack-able to restore this feature, it's a bit messy.

Lack of a KMS activation until servers are up again, so these among a few other things, have simply "turned me off" to the final build .. a few revisions will be made, the inability to circumvent the "Win 8 GUI - Formerly Known as "Metro"  has just tipped the scales to the ""meh" side of win 8 over win 7.

So, next time you "up," be a little more clear and I am sure your intentions will be better understood.
